if the program prints "repeated entires in the chemchk file" then no need to panic.
It is a sorting error in the chemchk file. Just ignore it. It will not change your
final result except the wiggles in the graph. I am working on correcting it.

If the program prints 'formation/destruction of this species does not exist' then
please do not panic or wonder you wrote the correct name. Just choose the name from
the lsit printed. Sometimes even if the molecule exist it does not mean that both 
formation and destruction of the molecule exist. One reaction is enough for a molecule
to be included in the chemical reaction network.

